GQEBERHA - South Africa is looking to wrap up the Test series against Bangladesh early after declaring their second innings on 176/6 on day three of the second Test. Bangladesh is chasing a target of 413 and will resume the day on 27/3. Teams: South Africa: Dean Elgar (capt), Sarel Erwee, Keegan Petersen, Temba Bavuma, Ryan Rickelton, Kyle Verreynne (wkt), Wiaan Mulder, Keshav Maharaj, Simon Harmer, Lizaad Williams, Duanne Olivier. Bangladesh: Mominul Haque (capt), Tamim Iqbal, Mahmudul Hasan, Najmul Hossain, Mushfiqur Rahim, Liton Das (wkt), Yasir Ali, Mehidy Hasan, Taijul Islam, Khaled Ahmed, Ebadot Hossain. LISTEN: SA vs Bangladesh, second Test, Day 4 